Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.82,0:02:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,growing, developing field, and we learn as we go.\NSo the initial naivete, and then therefore people who were not able to do it tried to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.07,0:03:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,do it and said it didn't work, and I couldn't understand why it didn't work because it worked\Nall the time, and in the video we did called Power Versus Force I think, you know, we used
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.53,0:03:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,naive children.\NSome people say it's suggestion, you know, but in that videotape we used naive children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.24,0:03:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't know who Hippocrates was or anybody was, you know.\NSo a naive child, it worked very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.88,0:03:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I must admit that was an ignorance on my part that I presumed everybody could do it.\NSo that's one of the errors of perception is you presume everybody's like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.69,0:03:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is, you know, eager to know the truth.\NYou know, for its own sake, and it was a crushing realization that most people do not
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.15,0:03:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,want to know truth for its own sake.\NThey really want a verification of what they already believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.73,0:04:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's enough of that rattling on.\NI guess my question is I always wanted to know how deep is hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.56,0:04:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it below the level of consciousness scale?\NCan you go below there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's extremely low.\NIt's a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.57,0:04:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually a different dimension.\NTherefore it's not really calibratable on that scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.43,0:04:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other dimensions other than the ones we are familiar with.\NThere are those astral levels, upper, middle, and lower, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.89,0:04:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are other dimensions, and I don't wish to do a scale for those dimensions, other\Ndimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.34,0:04:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So if a human chooses or keeps choosing, what does that mean?\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.34,0:04:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If a human chooses or keeps choosing to deny truth and fall in calibration, is there a\Npoint where they go to so low that one little spark of light has no chance to return?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.72,0:05:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like they're picked up as an easy pickings from other dimensions.\NThey call it demonic possession, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.08,0:05:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it actual life, part of life, or is it?\NIt's from a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Different dimension, okay.\NDifferent dimension, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.70,0:05:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But...\NIt's like paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other dimensions.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.70,0:05:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NVery good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.38,0:05:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou don't want to know about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.60,0:05:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You really don't want to know about them.\NLike the crime that was revealed about what this guy was going to do to this little girl
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.33,0:05:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,a week or two ago, you don't want to know where that came from.\NJust take my word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.46,0:05:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good there.\NThe hell that I went into was not...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.82,0:05:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a hospital.\NI was in a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.82,0:05:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not like that.\NWhat people depict as hell was the upper level.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:06:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's just the jacks for openers.\NThe real hell was far, far more horrible than that, but not in a linear way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.69,0:06:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was nonlinear and timeless, and it was not horror.\NIt was despair at a level of hopelessness that went on forever, and you experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.74,0:06:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,forever hopelessness.\NEons and eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.74,0:06:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eons and eons of timeless hopelessness, and it's beyond description.\NAll I can tell people is you don't want to go there at all, no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.30,0:06:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You just do not want to go there.\NYou do not want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.64,0:06:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we believe you.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.15,0:06:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that the intellect does not correlate with the level of consciousness.\NI know that intellectually, but in life, I tend to lose track of that fact, so I wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.18,0:06:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to know, to help with discernment, if you could talk a little bit about that.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.18,0:06:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.18,0:06:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.14,0:06:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to talk a little bit about the origin of the intellect?\NThe origin of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:07:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect.\NWell, that of course is evolutionary, with the emergence of the prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.24,0:07:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the advance of hominids, once the hominids stood up, then it had two limbs that\Nit didn't need for locomotion, and that gave it a tremendous advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.28,0:07:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the next genetic improvement was the oppositional thumb.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.20,0:07:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you've got an oppositional thumb, you can do tools.\NSo the emergence of the prefrontal cortex and the gray matter there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.03,0:07:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,standing on one's feet and freeing up the front two limbs,\Nso they were now available for exploration instead of locomotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.17,0:07:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You could begin to become acquainted with things, and you could now do things.\NSo the use of tools was very singular.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.40,0:08:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when Lucy came around, that was three million years ago,\Nthat was the beginning of what we call the modern hominid, you know, called man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.59,0:08:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So would the intellect carry over from one lifetime to the next?\NI don't know, dear, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean if you learn algebra in one lifetime, you won't have to learn it next?\NNo, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.71,0:08:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be nice, wouldn't it?\NTake algebra one lifetime, solid geometry the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.40,0:08:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, I've been working on surrendering the juice of the experiencer as things arise,\Nand finding it's a continuous process with seemingly no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.80,0:09:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a way, I guess I don't understand truly deep surrender to the point where it doesn't come up anymore?\NYes, no, it takes years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.84,0:09:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget my own evolution of years.\NPersistence is what pays off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.47,0:09:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually it runs out.\NNow you see the peculiar thing about the whole thought of I,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.93,0:09:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see that the experiencer is trying to constantly fortress the reality of something separate called I.\NSo when you say I, in a way you're talking about greediness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.12,0:09:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Greediness for claim.\NIt's a whole subject in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.39,0:10:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I could write a book, well I started to write a book about it, I did one time, called I, I think.\NAnyway, the I is, I can't write on that, it's some kind of a disc thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.10,0:10:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The I intrinsically is craving, and it claims authorship and ownership.\NAnd it's constantly looking to reinforce, reforce itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.60,0:10:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason it has to constantly reinforce itself is because it's based on an illusion.\NIf it was based on a reality, it wouldn't have any interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.19,0:11:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's always claiming that I did this, I thought that.\NThe, if you meditate on the concept I, period, just do nothing but hold I, and be with I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I-ness, and see what happens.\NRight, there's nothingness, then, or allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.56,0:11:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are concepts, I told you to just stay with I.\NJust stay with I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.24,0:11:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're elaborating already.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.24,0:11:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stay with I-ness.\NI-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of it, the feelingness, the location, stay with I-ness, and see what happens.\NAnd don't call it anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.96,0:11:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NNo, that's clustering it all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.56,0:11:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NJust stay with I-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I.\NNot your thoughts about I, but the essence of I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:12:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will see, it will dissolve, and you'll be left with that out of which I-ness arises.\NWe'll call you Swami, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.19,0:12:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Swami.\NSwami-I.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.90,0:12:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Doc.\NIt seems to me that there's a fine line between surrendering everything to God and apathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.37,0:12:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm struggling a bit with, you know, why should I do things, when should I do things,\Nyou know, even when I try to...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.54,0:12:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's futility.\NThat's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.74,0:12:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're labeling it as futile, or useless, or not worth anything.\NSurrendering it means control, surrendering control of it, surrendering control of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.01,0:13:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendering trying to juice it, allowing everything to just be as it is.\NSo, I would just continue to do what I think is right to do, and surrender the outcome?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.17,0:13:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a neat phrase for it.\NYou're responsible for the effort, but not the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.86,0:13:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So result means trying to control, you know, trying to control, say, because you dedicate\Nyour efforts to God, and then whatever is, is whatever is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.76,0:13:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's karma yoga.\NKarma yoga means selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.76,0:13:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not looking at God.\NYou're looking at yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.44,0:13:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not looking for any payoff.\NYou're not looking for any gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.44,0:13:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You do it for the sake of doing it.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you do it because you're the steward of certain talents, you know?\NIf you're a great pianist, you do it because that's your talent, and you're the steward
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.33,0:13:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of that talent.\NSo you give your musicality to the world as a result of your stewardship of that gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NDr. Hawkins, does feeling the sensations of the body play a role in kind of, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.28,0:14:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a role in contemplation?\NIt's something you have to, like, learn how to handle and transcend, just like you do
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.47,0:14:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in meditation.\NAnd eventually, then you discover the spontaneous, that the body and its functions are spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and autonomous, as you let go, trying to control them or resist them.\NAnd you just accept that that's the way that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.10,0:14:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, a horse is what it is.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.42,0:14:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't try and change the horse, but you accept the nature of the horse.\NSo you accept the nature of this protoplasmic embodiment, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.42,0:14:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to make concessions to the limitations of protoplasm.\NProtoplasm can only stand so much, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.38,0:15:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you learn to live within the limitations.\NIt's one of the reasons I say it's difficult to be a human, because you have the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,aspects.\NYou've got the intellectual concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.57,0:15:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got the emotionality to deal with.\NYou've got all the yeses and the noes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.57,0:15:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got all the training, the brainwashing.\NOn top of all that, you've got this pile of protoplasm to look after.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.57,0:15:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It keeps you busy, you know what I'm saying?\NWhen you're scratching your toe, you're trying to remember your mother-in-law's birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.57,0:15:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't remember it, and you feel guilty about that.\NYou're trying to process that, and just then, you start to sneeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.57,0:15:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,On the way here this morning, there was something that went right out of my mind.\NAnd it was, you know, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.01,0:15:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.01,0:15:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.01,0:15:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.01,0:15:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably a kitty hair, you know.\NI couldn't get it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.01,0:15:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried pulling it this way, had to go get an eye cup and wash it out.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just what I need as I'm leaving the driveway, you know, is to have to wash your\Neye out, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.01,0:15:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminded God.\NI said, you know, it is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.53,0:16:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of being a human.\NOh, Lordy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ever get where we're going,\Nwe've earned it, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.00,0:16:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great accomplishment, I think,\Nto complete a human lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and it really is demanding on so many levels.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.09,0:16:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, you had said before\Nthat sometimes God uses our minds to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.91,0:16:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we tell the difference\Nbetween when it is God who is using our mind to think
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.35,0:16:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we are doing our own chatter?\NWell, it's sort of a languaging problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.32,0:17:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say realizations\Nthat are benevolent and holistic
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.02,0:17:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and tend to heal, etc.,\None could ascribe them as coming from a higher source.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.53,0:17:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to be God personally.\NBut the radiance of that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.06,0:17:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to...\Nfavor thoughts of a certain direction
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.62,0:17:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and not favor thoughts in the opposite direction.\NSo I never see it as causation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.87,0:17:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I see it as likelihood, potentiality.\NYou know, the intention of becoming spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.52,0:17:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,increases the potentiality\Nthat certain thoughts are going to be more common
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.02,0:17:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,than they would be in a person who lacks that intention.\NBut they're not caused by the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.41,0:17:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more likelihood.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.91,0:18:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality rather than likelihood.\NIt's really, in a way, physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.28,0:18:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Advanced theoretical physics.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.42,0:18:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The question that I had was in reference\Nto something that I read in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.88,0:18:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcending the Levels of Consciousness.\NYou talk about surrender and devotion and faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.58,0:18:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would just like for you to,\Nif you would, expand a little bit on the faith
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.98,0:18:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and its faith in what?\NFaith is an aspect of personality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.86,0:18:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,without which we can...\Nwithout which you couldn't live, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.46,0:18:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You have faith in all kinds of things all the time.\NEvery time you put your foot down,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.50,0:18:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you have faith that your ankle's gonna hold you up.\NSo faith is really operative.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.68,0:18:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with expectation and expected reliability.\NI can't do anything except write my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.26,0:19:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual faith is something different.\NSpiritual faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.98,0:19:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Placing your faith and hope in things unseen is trust.\NSo that's really trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.22,0:19:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to trust.\NPlacing your faith in things unseen, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.36,0:19:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,comes as an inspiration to do that.\NNow, to do that already increases the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.16,0:19:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of the fulfillment of that.\NNot from a causal viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.28,0:19:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NBut then you have the likelihood of it is increased
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.16,0:19:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,by your commitment and your intention\Nthat the response is going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.78,0:19:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,more positive.\NMore probable in a certain direction than another.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.46,0:20:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're affecting probability by intention.\NSo, trusting that the paths in front of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the teachers that were the way-showers,\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.64,0:20:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That that's a safe path to follow.\NIs that the faith that you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.94,0:20:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we go even farther than faith.\NBecause we look at the modern mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.44,0:20:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The modern mind would like some kind of mathematical\Nor logical or intellectual proof as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.08,0:20:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThey would like to have it backed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.44,0:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith, without good works, you know, is empty.\NSo, faith for its own sake, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.00,0:20:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is already a certain kind of sacredness, is it not?\NI think ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.78,0:20:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it is.\NAnd you're not looking for payoffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.08,0:20:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's sort of like karma yoga\Nin that you do it for its own sake
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.26,0:20:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and not for some gain, to be gained by thereby.\NBut thereby you fulfill your own potential to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.67,0:21:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The skeptic has no belief in faith at all.\NHe ridicules faith, except in his own skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.09,0:21:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And he has great faith in that.\NI get a kick out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.25,0:21:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NDo you know there's that saying that God has a,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.52,0:21:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it, tell God you have a plan\Nand what is the sense of humor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.60,0:21:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell God you have a plan and then everything just gets messed up.\NAnd today I plan to go into the, on top of that, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.00,0:21:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to the ocean.\Non Shelby Road the other way
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.48,0:21:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and just sit up there and contemplate\Nand then for some reason Tim picked up a book
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought this was a humorous book\Nthis Scorpion book
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.32,0:21:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,well it changed my experience sitting up in the Red Rocks\NI will tell you that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.42,0:21:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that was quite overwhelming\Nbut then I wanted to share with you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.28,0:22:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that somehow the self gets me here\NI'm not sure how that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.73,0:22:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because I get in your presence\Nand I really have a hard time functioning
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.45,0:22:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a hard time what?\Nwho asked you to function?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.76,0:22:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,she just asks questions\Nbut yet I crave this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.04,0:22:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I hike in the mornings\NI don't know how I get out there
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.38,0:22:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or how I get back\Nbut I'm always by myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.80,0:22:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there's not an audience\Nand my spiritual stuff is kind of private
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.78,0:22:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but then I get in your presence\Nand I come here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.72,0:22:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just crave coming into this energy field\Nand then I just want to be here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.53,0:22:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all I know\NI know what you mean
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.15,0:22:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't really have a question or a story or anything\NI just want to be here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.79,0:22:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that's very common\Nbecause you come with a question
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.85,0:22:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but in a certain energy field\Nthe question dissolves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.05,0:22:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's not a question\NI don't even have a question
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.73,0:23:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know I don't even have a question\NI just want to sit here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.49,0:23:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to be someplace\Nwhere I have
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.27,0:23:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,where it's familiar\Nand people understand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.61,0:23:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because of your own intention\Nyou reflect that fact like a pool
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.69,0:23:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that ripples in a pool to yourself\Nthat's your own self
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.41,0:23:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,bouncing off of myself\Nso now you're only experiencing your own self
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.24,0:23:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,well\Nwhatever
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.64,0:23:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this happens when I get around you\NI did a seminar with you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.98,0:23:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it was in Palm Springs\Nand you're usually wired up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.90,0:23:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and you didn't ever leave the stage before\Nand I was sitting on a row seat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.90,0:23:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had my eyes closed\Njust sort of taking your energy in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.90,0:23:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and then all of a sudden\Nwith my eyes closed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.90,0:23:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I had goosebumps on my arms\Nand the hair on my neck went up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.90,0:23:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I started having problems breathing\Nand then I was getting teary
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.90,0:23:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I finally opened my eyes\Nlike what is going on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.90,0:23:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and you were standing next to me\Nand every time I get in this presence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.90,0:23:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this happens\Nand it's just
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.80,0:24:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a phenomena\Nit's a phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.80,0:24:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a phenomena\NI will tell you that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.80,0:24:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's just wonderful\Nand I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.80,0:24:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what I would do without you\Nit's autonomous
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.80,0:24:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it occurs in the spiritual world\Nit's autonomous
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.80,0:24:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it happens of its own\NI don't know what I would do without your teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.80,0:24:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because I would be\Nthey're wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.21,0:24:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they just help me know\Nwhat's going on in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.21,0:24:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and I go\Noh that's what's important
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.21,0:24:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that's because of who you are\Nno
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.21,0:24:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if you were somebody else\Nyou'd think I'm a nuisance
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.85,0:24:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I am like\NI
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.93,0:24:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I put your video going\Nand I go
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.93,0:24:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you God\Nthank you for this man
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.93,0:24:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,God thank you for this man\Neverything makes sense
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.93,0:24:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,when I listen to your words\Nso thank you God
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.93,0:24:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nbecause you're aligned with divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.93,0:24:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in this way\Nthank you very much
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.93,0:24:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,if you were not with baseball\Nyou wouldn't feel that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.93,0:24:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not much on the ball field\NI can't see the ball coming at me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.68,0:24:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why they\Nthey wouldn't let me on the field
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.68,0:24:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins\Nthank you so much for your books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.68,0:25:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I live to read them every day\Nand they've certainly transformed my life
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.68,0:25:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right now I'm dealing with something\Nthat you have dealt with
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.68,0:25:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps I can gain some insight\Nfrom you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.68,0:25:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how to go about\Ndealing with this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.68,0:25:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with chronic pain\Nand potential
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.68,0:25:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a great potential\Nfor physical disability
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.68,0:25:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems inevitable\NI've tried a lot of things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.68,0:25:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,allopathic\Nand alternative medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.68,0:25:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it seems to be\Na degenerative process
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.68,0:25:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so you know\Nbeing very galvanized
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.68,0:25:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you're mentally degenerating\Nmentally degenerating
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.68,0:25:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,on top of it\Ngood luck to you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.68,0:25:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right\Nhappy imbecile
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.68,0:25:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,happy\Nvery happy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.68,0:25:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what I'd like to be\Nis happily
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.68,0:25:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,happy\Nhappy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.68,0:25:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,happy\Nhappy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.71,0:25:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,happy\Nhappy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.71,0:25:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,happy\Nhappy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.71,0:25:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is happily in pain\Nis it possible
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.71,0:25:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how does\NI guess what I'm asking
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.71,0:25:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you\Ntranscended
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.71,0:25:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pain\Nand of course
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.71,0:25:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I would not put myself\Nat the same level
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.71,0:25:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nthat I could
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.71,0:25:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but are there any directions\Nfor dealing with it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.71,0:25:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can actually\Nfunction in life
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.71,0:26:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and do things\Nother than
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.71,0:26:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't label it\Npain anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.71,0:26:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not experiencing pain\Npain is a concept
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.81,0:26:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a thought\Nsee
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.81,0:26:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,there are certain sensations\Ncoming up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.87,0:26:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do is you completely surrender and let go any resistance you become one\Nwith the sensation and you thereby disappear them because you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.50,0:26:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,experience that which is not resisted so I've tried that I didn't say this is\Ntaking me years but just that's the idea is to constantly surrender also clear
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.52,0:26:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,anything in yourself that you think suspect karmically might be an\Nunderpinning of it you understand what I'm saying when you say surrender do you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.52,0:27:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,mean somehow forgive it within yourself admit it thank you I think that answers\Nit I will proceed and hope it all just dissolves away
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.38,0:27:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,next time I see you sometimes the serious thing to do is to ask for\Nforgiveness for that within within yourself of which you no longer recall
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.31,0:27:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which brought such things to others well Lord forgive me for having brought\Nsuffering pain into the life of others sometimes I think out of guilt out of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.40,0:27:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the pain you've brought into the life of others which you've forgotten you bring\Nit upon yourself and once you forgive yourself for that tends to receive
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.66,0:27:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiveness and a POWERFULness all the time\Nit's kind of the fire I'm looking at you different and I thought well you know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.36,0:28:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,he's you're big in real life you're like this\NI believe I am a baby compared to midgets yes that's why I like going to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.21,0:28:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Korea everybody was my height\NReally, I felt like a big man. I looked down and everybody was about the same level I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.07,0:28:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pow!\NThis is neat. This is like a six-footer must feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.07,0:28:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\NFirst of all, my sister wanted to say she loves you a lot, and thank you very much because you changed her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.07,0:28:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And all she's read is Power vs. Force.\NAnd also friends from Maui, Hawaii send their love.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.07,0:29:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And I love you very much.\NMy question is, you often talk about having stewardship of one's gifts and one's assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.87,0:29:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What if all you have is debt and you don't know what your gifts are?\NAnd what?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.87,0:29:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't know what your gifts are.\NWell, to begin with, debts, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.30,0:29:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because debts become a motivator, do they not?\NYeah, you don't want to have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.48,0:29:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do debts mean?\NWhat do debts lead you to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.70,0:29:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to work.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.54,0:29:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask Broccoli.\NWhat did Broccoli say?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.21,0:29:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to work.\NGet a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.98,0:29:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting in my study and all of a sudden Broccoli would go, go to work.\NGet a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.30,0:29:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Brings me up every time.\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.36,0:29:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's actually, it's not the debts that are the problem.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.36,0:29:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The debts themselves are just the debts.\NThey come, they go.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.36,0:29:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's good.\NIt's more not really having an idea of what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.36,0:30:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,An idea of what the gifts are.\NYou know, stewardship of one's gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.36,0:30:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I would love to be a steward of my gifts, but I don't know what they are.\NYou don't have any gifts?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.36,0:30:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm sure I do somewhere, but...\NYou need a gift therapist, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.36,0:30:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You are my gift therapist.\NYou got nice teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.36,0:30:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You still got your face?\NYou haven't had plastic surgery?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.36,0:30:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIs that a new nose made out of cartilage from your knee?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.36,0:30:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIt's all, it's all...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.36,0:30:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you don't wear glasses.\NWell, I had surgery there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.36,0:30:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the...\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.36,0:30:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the surgery.\NI had the surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.36,0:30:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the surgery.\NI had the surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.36,0:30:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the surgery.\NI had the surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.36,0:30:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the surgery.\NI had the LASIK surgery there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.26,0:30:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you see all right?\NYeah, I see pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd you got a full head of hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.26,0:30:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDo you have carcinoma anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.26,0:30:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't even know what that is.\NYou have health, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.26,0:30:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty good.\NYou don't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.26,0:30:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Pain.\NI have pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.26,0:30:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NI have pain, but yeah, I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.26,0:30:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have...\NYou have physical aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.52,0:30:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How old are you?\NForty-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.52,0:30:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, you still have youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.52,0:30:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, but as far as I'm concerned, I don't have any physical aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.68,0:31:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You have youth.\NYou have aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.68,0:31:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You have health.\NYou have good teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.68,0:31:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a job?\NYes, I have a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.68,0:31:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have a job?\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.68,0:31:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Good golly, what more do you want?\NNo, I don't want gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.68,0:31:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You got friends?\NYeah, wonderful, beautiful friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.68,0:31:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, is there something more beyond the lens?\NWell, I guess what I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.68,0:31:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm trying to understand is it's like...\NYou're probably thinking of a special person.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.68,0:31:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.68,0:31:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.90,0:31:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.90,0:31:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.90,0:31:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.90,0:31:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.03,0:31:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.03,0:31:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.03,0:31:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.03,0:31:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.41,0:31:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.48,0:31:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.48,0:31:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.76,0:31:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.76,0:31:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.76,0:31:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.76,0:31:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.76,0:31:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,More of like, a way of being of service in the world as...\NYou know, like, is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.76,0:31:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I have to do, is just do what I'm doing?\NIt seems like there's so much more...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.76,0:31:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I think so.\NIf you're friendly and kind and benign to the world, think how exceptional you are already.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.76,0:31:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember from that chart in the pyramid?\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.86,0:32:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people in the world just to be benign and kind and friendly and open and helpful helpful\Nlittle ladies crossing the street you know what i'm saying yeah i do always take a little while
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.26,0:32:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to label these so you think it gives us something exceptional maybe that's the thing\Nyeah it's all dark and handsome and rich you see a famous movie star i guess i just feel like like
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.62,0:32:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,i like um you have good health you walk around you've got a pacemaker i mean you're way ahead\Nof the game i guess it's in striving to do in striving to do more that's all it's just wanting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.98,0:33:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a better person well the intention is sufficient and then you ask god to reveal to you\Nmore okay you're trying to use your thinker to get it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.40,0:33:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,forget it\Nthinker. That which you are is your gift to the world. You understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.71,0:33:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAre you safe to be in a boat with?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.74,0:33:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.\NYou don't stand up in a canoe?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.74,0:33:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou're way ahead of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.79,0:33:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have a charming smile.\NI want to say that I've been reading your books a lot. I'm up to the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.74,0:34:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The growth between ten years ago and now is phenomenal because I was reading people like Thomas Troward and Ralph Waldo Emerson.\NBecause I'm a religious scientist and practitioner.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.74,0:34:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'm teaching that class and now I actually understand it.\NIt was like,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.96,0:34:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like I did it because I had to do it.\NOh, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.96,0:34:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's just,\NYou get meaning behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.96,0:34:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What a gift.\NWhat a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.96,0:34:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These teachings have made very clear things that were so confused.\NI'm able to actually hold a line of thought until the end of the sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.96,0:34:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That may sound like amazing, but because of your type of writing.\NNow transcendentalism means more to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.60,0:34:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, this is, I don't know if it's a question or it's just a confirmation.\NI've been involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.86,0:34:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been involved in NLP and timeline therapy.\NI don't know if you know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.86,0:34:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a teaching derived from Huna.\NAnd I've been doing a workshop,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.86,0:34:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which I vowed back 13 years ago to do at least one a year.\NAnd it's about emotional freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.05,0:35:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the name of my workshop is Emotional Freedom by Giving Yourself a Second Opinion.\NSo I do this and I do this with my church group.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.05,0:35:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just wondering,\NI think I know,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.05,0:35:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm just going to ask you anyway.\NThere's karmic consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.40,0:35:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for everything, right?\NWhat we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.40,0:35:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And, but then again, there was,\NI heard you say today that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.40,0:35:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not exactly tit for tat or life for life.\NNo, it's not cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.40,0:35:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.\NIt's likelihood and potentialities.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.40,0:35:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Okay, so that's good.\NAnd so I'm thinking if you work with someone
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.40,0:35:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and they release a lot of karma,\Nand they don't have to go the whole tit for tat route,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.40,0:35:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is that okay?\NKarmically in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.63,0:35:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.17,0:35:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we only have it to be done with their willingness and their assent.\NYou're not doing it against their will.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.17,0:35:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, oh yeah.\NThat's absolutely the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.17,0:35:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.59,0:35:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it.\NI'm doing another two workshops this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.59,0:35:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAnyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.59,0:35:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.91,0:36:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,God in his ultimate mercy gives us a chance to undo our errors.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.91,0:36:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.94,0:36:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe'll move faster then.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.04,0:36:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.19,0:36:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.19,0:36:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So in all of your books you have them calibrated by chapter,\Nexcept for transcending.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.60,0:36:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because each chapter is already about a calibrated level.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.60,0:36:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So then even though the lower calibrated chapters would still calibrate low?\NNo, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.37,0:36:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a separate number.\NYeah, but I mean the description, the analysis of it would be of a different calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.56,0:36:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.56,0:36:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.56,0:37:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I just thought that was really curious.\NBecause I like the fact that each, like in the first one, power versus force, you talked
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.36,0:37:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about how you went through each paragraph and sentence and discovered like the one with\Nthe John Lennon.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.36,0:37:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NLine and everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.36,0:37:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NIt's really interesting because I have, kinesiology is very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.36,0:37:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.36,0:37:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've enjoyed your books very much and I love you.\NI'm glad you enjoyed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.36,0:37:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.36,0:37:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,From the Chicago area.\NIn fact, I'm part of a group that promotes, you know, it's a spiritual, a new spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.36,0:37:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,group that talks about your books.\NAnd I brought you a present.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.40,0:37:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a book I wrote.\NOh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.40,0:37:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Dedicated to you.\NHey.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.62,0:37:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you very much.\NYou're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.62,0:37:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.\NYou're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.62,0:37:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.\NYou're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.62,0:37:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.\NYou're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.62,0:38:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.\NYou're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.62,0:38:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And a question I had for you, doctor.\NCould I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.00,0:38:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I?\NCould I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.29,0:38:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he say?\NCan I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.49,0:38:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hug my hand.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.49,0:38:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.\NI'll tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.49,0:38:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all my bones have turned to Styrofoam.\NYou understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.00,0:38:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you.\NThank you very much for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.19,0:38:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'm doing everything to recalcify the skillet.\NI never paid much attention to the body, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.87,0:38:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've done a lot more work.\Nand now I'm learning you've got to pay attention to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.90,0:38:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise it's going to be a drag.\NI understand all the bad things I put in this body.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.15,0:38:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NDo you want to get a picture with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.69,0:38:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.48,0:39:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NBeyond words.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.29,0:39:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So my question is about devotional non-duality.\NI think.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.80,0:39:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And for me, how to live on the razor's edge.\NFrom your teachings, the opening, letting go into the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.04,0:39:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the spontaneity emerging, all the beauty, desire for enlightenment, so what?\NThe city, so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.51,0:39:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it, so what?\NAnd recently, as I've been dealing,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.56,0:40:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been deeply quiet, spontaneously, I reach a place inside\Nwhere I think I've met the essence of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.44,0:40:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the density that doesn't surrender.\NIt has to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.00,0:40:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI'll take you up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.14,0:40:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the razor's edge?\NYou follow the razor's edge, and it'll take it to the core of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.76,0:40:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ego's belief that it is your creator,\Nand your source of life, and you surrender that to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.04,0:40:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you go through a period that you'll die.\NWhen I'm anywhere close to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.73,0:40:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, honey, I don't know.\NIt's just a whole evolutionary phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.11,0:40:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not linear, so you can't say,\Nwell, if you're here, now this is coming next.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.95,0:41:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like fields interacting with fields.\NSo this field here potentiates all the fields within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.15,0:41:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this field is this way, and this field is this way.\NWell, the field is empowering every one of these fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.67,0:41:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So if this is empowered this way,\Nit's even more this way than it would have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.77,0:41:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's overlapping coexistence fields of influence.\NIt's more like a complicated interaction of fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.35,0:41:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you did that, didn't you?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.39,0:41:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway.\NThe likelihoods, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.67,0:41:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So each field is a potentializing,\Nand there are multiple interacting fields co-influencing phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.40,0:41:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from not only the past, but the present,\Nfrom fields beyond fields beyond fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.20,0:42:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond which is divinity itself,\Nthe infinite omnipresent field,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.49,0:42:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which empowers all the lesser fields.\NSo you're doing fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.78,0:42:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing fine.\NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.20,0:42:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about a thing.\NJust keep doing what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.36,0:42:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou're doing fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.58,0:42:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Fields within fields within fields.\NCan you close the doors?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.09,0:42:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We're losing our air conditioning.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.37,0:42:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've enjoyed your work for many years.\NThis is the first time for me to be here,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.77,0:42:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm very pleased and excited.\NI want to thank both of you and your team.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.52,0:42:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is quite a bit of experience in living in a communal setting,\Nand...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.15,0:42:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is exquisite for all that you do,\Nand the details I have great appreciation for.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.97,0:43:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my whole life been highly interested in spiritual evolving.\NAnd one of the things that has caught my passion for a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.88,0:43:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the major religions, there is reference to the Golden Age.\NGolden Age?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.34,0:43:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Golden Age, which means...\NHistorical age, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.68,0:43:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It means going back before the fall of man,\Nwhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.50,0:43:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?\NWhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.10,0:43:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?\NWhere humanity functioned in full consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.14,0:43:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,full divine function.\NI wonder, especially with what you bring,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.68,0:43:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if this awakening that I am going through and we're going through\Nis a gateway of some sort to bring back this Golden Age,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.37,0:44:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not like it used to be, but in a new way.\NI have no reason to presume that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.38,0:44:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The previous age was...\NIt was vulnerable, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.42,0:44:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to recreate that which failed the test?\NI don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.62,0:44:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like a future where the fall of man is not a potentiality or even a likelihood.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.99,0:44:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NForget the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.49,0:44:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Past is all illusion.\NThe ego was the cause of the fall, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.86,0:44:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou don't want to create which was, which failed miserably?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.68,0:44:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.68,0:44:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to create that which is immune to.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.68,0:45:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To the\Nnegativity and temptation and ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.97,0:45:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the naivete of Eve.\Nnumber of years now and I wondered if you're planning to have a lecture series
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.40,0:45:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,next year. We're in the planning stage of next year. This year we're trying as\Nevery other month. We'll probably still do every other month and then the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.67,0:45:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,workshop in the month in between. That was that everybody liked that a great\Ndeal. Real old-fashioned sad saying you know question answer discourse. I like
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.88,0:46:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,walking through the crowd and having a spontaneous conversation with everybody.\NThat's what I like the best. How about books? How about books? Books I'm planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.86,0:46:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Yes I told you we're doing an atlas of a hundred charts. We have lectures on\Nhealing and recovery which is gonna be out probably after the devotional nonduality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.20,0:46:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's spirituality and modern land.\NHealing?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.12,0:46:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the old-fashioned religion doesn't appeal to modern man.\NNeither does skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.74,0:46:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Skepticism does not fulfill him either.\NThe Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.54,0:46:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,These men are feeling unsatisfied and unfulfilled.\NSo what would be a spiritual pathway for a modern man
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.17,0:47:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,who isn't a peasant tending sheep on the desert 3,000 or 4,000 years ago?\NWhat appealed to him is idiotic to the modern man.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.12,0:47:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Bush lit up and started talking to him.\NGive me a break, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.48,0:47:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Swallowed by a whale in, say, three days.\NI mean, come on already.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.34,0:47:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So this forthcoming book is going to be a takeoff from the Scopes trial.\NThe Scopes trial was never resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.56,0:47:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They never resolved the argument.\NThey simply avoided addressing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.96,0:47:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He attacked his character.\NThe question was never answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.86,0:47:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What can modern man hold on to\Nand not look like an idiot through old-fashioned religion?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.10,0:47:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be intelligent, scientific,\Nand also spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.30,0:47:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and religious?\NThat's modern man's dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.98,0:47:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the problem I tend to address.\NI want to pick it up from the Scopes trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.20,0:47:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in the 20s,\Nand nobody has answered it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.70,0:47:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.\NYou've got to pick one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.72,0:48:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Old-fashioned religion.\NCan I do a picture with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.68,0:48:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd you see the dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.81,0:48:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Old-fashioned religion,\Nwhich appeals to the scientific mind
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.93,0:48:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is to the ignorant dummies out in the country,\Nrustic folks,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.02,0:48:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or else scientific skepticism.\NI mean, where is the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.16,0:48:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that embraces modern man?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.58,0:48:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.83,0:48:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm eager to write right now.\NEverything else that gets in the way of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.35,0:48:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm impatient to get through it.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.76,0:48:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if you would be willing\Nto calibrate something for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.64,0:48:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.64,0:48:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, we don't.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.56,0:48:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I do have a question.\NWhen you talk about,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.25,0:49:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember which book it's in now,\Nbut no need to do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.18,0:49:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the causality that is.\NNo need to meditate,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.50,0:49:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,no need to be an activist\Nfor change in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.47,0:49:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What motivates us?\NHow do we maintain motivation?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.35,0:49:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're quoting.\NYou say no need for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.98,0:49:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.40,0:49:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was one of your...\NYou're describing passivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.04,0:49:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my perception of what I read,\Nso it very likely was misperceived.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.68,0:49:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering a thing to God\Nis not the same thing as apathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.06,0:49:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're accountable for is the intention\Nand not the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.58,0:49:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The result is up to God.\NSo you do what you can to help people help themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.14,0:49:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it's up to them\Nbecause you don't want the karmic responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.82,0:50:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or controlling other people as far as outcome.\NYou can lead them to water,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.48,0:50:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can't make them drink.\NIt's a horse's karma whether he drinks or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.88,0:50:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Your karma is really to provide the water.\NSo it's defining what is your responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.40,0:50:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,towards yourself and others.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.90,0:50:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To give yourself and others the best opportunity you can\Nfor the highest level of love that you can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.16,0:50:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the most loving thing is to let them be.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.07,0:50:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Tough love.\NTough love.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.93,0:50:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tough love.\NLet them be.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.41,0:50:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about surfing.\NActually, it's sort of like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.05,0:50:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Living in causality is like surfing life.\NYes, you got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.59,0:50:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Surfing is very much like surfing.\NIt's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.89,0:50:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI'm going to move you because you're right in that light.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.89,0:50:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What light?\NBehind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.17,0:50:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to move this light just slightly.\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.76,0:50:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a filming thing, guys.\NThat was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.98,0:51:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hop, hop, hop, hop, hop.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.00,0:51:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first found your work,\Nit started to smooth out my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.28,0:51:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And fill in a lot of the gaps.\NI went along a little further.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.55,0:51:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, just about every aspect is in complete and total upheaval.\NYou know, being here, I think I've heard this story now from some other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.71,0:51:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NI'm not exactly sure how to go forward every day, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.42,0:51:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You just follow basic spiritual principles.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.22,0:51:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My hardest role, or what I perceive to be my hardest role right now,\Nis the mother of a 16-year-old.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.66,0:51:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's in...\NI mean, this is my third child.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.96,0:52:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I knew what I was doing until now.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.69,0:52:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that I'm in such upheaval and everything changing in my life\Nand in these roles,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.08,0:52:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking to see if anybody has any questions.\NAnybody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.86,0:52:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody else?\NAnybody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.02,0:52:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody else?\NAnybody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.16,0:52:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,has any wisdom, because I'm having difficulty understanding and parenting, where you stop,\Nwhere you kind of stop, you know, where you start turning it over to them, and let them
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.51,0:52:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,live their life, and not, because I don't have the answers anymore.\NTo what?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.67,0:52:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're very mysterious about all this, I mean, what are you talking about, big turns, your\Nlife is all topsy-turvy about life?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.43,0:52:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, you know, everything has changed my...\NLike what?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.45,0:53:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Religious affiliation, where I live, my relationship with my husband, every person in my family,\Nall the people that I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.18,0:53:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it's like getting a divorce, right?\NIt totally changes everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.46,0:53:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the whole, everything, yeah.\NQuitting a job, moving to a different country.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.34,0:53:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it feels like that.\NYeah, so what's your question, is what is the role of a parent?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.26,0:53:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah, a parent who's going through all this, who's now having trouble,\Nwhere the answers were simple before, they've gotten so much more complex, and I just wondered
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.51,0:53:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if...\NYou got a therapist?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.51,0:53:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NWell, you need one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.47,0:53:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.47,0:53:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Practically.\NYou're honest with a 16-year-old, you just tell him, I don't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.47,0:53:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The practicality is that I only have a therapist, I mean, the complexity you're describing,\Nwhat's the role of a parent?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.16,0:53:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah, to try and influence a kid in a certain direction without controlling them, but I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.75,0:53:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,really think a therapist would be helpful to you right now.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.35,0:54:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not very true.\NThat's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.35,0:54:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I needed to hear.\NReally psychological, emotional, not spiritual, really, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.46,0:54:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Adjustment problems.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.78,0:54:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe spiritual seems to have stirred it all up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.78,0:54:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.49,0:54:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt's like you're going through...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.78,0:54:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that going through it isn't easy.\NMm-mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.57,0:54:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NWell, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.57,0:54:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention is to do the best you can in all these various roles.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.76,0:54:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But you need somebody that you can give feedback about the details, and not generalities.\NSee, with me here, you're going to have to do a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.76,0:54:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.76,0:54:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.76,0:54:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.76,0:54:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.76,0:54:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.76,0:54:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.76,0:54:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.08,0:54:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.59,0:54:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.59,0:54:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll look.\NYou can do it piecemeal, piece by piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.59,0:54:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this?\NWhat about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.59,0:54:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What about that?\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.59,0:54:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.17,0:54:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I would do.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.90,0:54:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.90,0:55:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain times in your life when having a therapist is like having a best\Nfriend, and it's somebody you can trust and discuss things with, and discuss it at a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.90,0:55:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,different level than personal relationships.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.90,0:55:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. My question was about what exactly is your level of consciousness? Is it like an average of all your attributes or is it one thing?\NOverall field, yeah. That's what I thought. It was just at a study group we were having a conversation and there were some disagreements so I thought I'd ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.39,0:55:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, different archetypal roles within yourself may have evolved to different levels. The student in you might be quite involved. The devotee might be quite involved.\NSo the various roles that you have within yourself, some will be more advanced than others, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.55,0:56:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you calibrated them differently, you know, my social person, what does it calibrate at? What does my student calibrate at?\NYou might find yourself more advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.74,0:56:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Your student is quite far advanced. Your social person is retarded. It might be the other way around.\NYou're a cool extrovert, but when it comes to studentship, you know, you're not well-motivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.74,0:56:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could examine different aspects of your personality and calibrate them independently.\NI'll try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.90,0:56:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it'd be fun to get to know, you know, where are your high points and where are your low points. Are you familiar with Carl Jung and the, you know?\NThat sounds familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.00,0:56:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay, never mind.\NI guess it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.00,0:56:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You could look at the different aspects of your personality. What's the calibrated level of your friend, you know, being the friend to others?\NThe student, the son, the lover, the various roles that you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.38,0:56:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How good a neighbor are you? You know what I'm saying?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.38,0:57:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, there are people, there are neighbors so bad that people shoot them.\NI sure hope I'm not one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.42,0:57:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a guy, an old man who lived in an apartment, he was 90, in New York City, and the SOB next door would not stop playing his radio loud at night.\NSo he took a shotgun and killed him dead in a mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.06,0:57:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So the guy who played the radio loud was not being a good neighbor.\NNow he is. He's a very quiet neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.02,0:57:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I sympathize with the old guy.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.37,0:57:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably deserved it, you know.\NYou often talk about when a person reaches a level of 600 and half of them decide not to stay and half of them stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.42,0:58:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so.\NSo, if this S and so forth is 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.45,0:58:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is 600 and it dies and goes to the other side, the body dies, then does the body have to come back here?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.45,0:58:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know?\NI'm not in the body shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.45,0:58:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's a free elective. It's a free elective.\NIt's a free elective.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.45,0:58:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very clear that there's no obligation in any direction.\NIt's all a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.74,0:58:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no gain.\NNothing gained and nothing lost in either direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.95,0:58:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.07,0:58:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.09,0:58:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's an open door.\NIt's okay to walk through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.59,0:58:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is very clear.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.46,0:59:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI wanted to ask you about deja vu.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.18,0:59:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have an explanation for it because I haven't looked at it.\NI don't know whether it's a neurological doubling back and it's an illusion that you've experienced it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.24,0:59:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had it a couple of times.\NI've had it a couple of times in my life and it was quite real.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.36,0:59:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The certainty that you've experienced this before, whereas in fact I know it was not\Npossible, but the experiential was that you've experienced this exactly before.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.65,0:59:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the clock being at the same time.\NI don't have an explanation because I haven't really researched it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.11,0:59:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm suspecting it's some kind of a time doubling illusion.\NI'm just suspecting that neurologically.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.46,1:00:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So something just don't necessarily pay attention to?\NI don't know the explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.42,1:00:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBut I've had it and it's very real.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.42,1:00:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it seems real.\NI had it in World War II when I was on the troop ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.42,1:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The train broke down in Golden, Colorado.\NIt took four hours to fix it, the whole troop train.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.00,1:00:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We all got off.\NWe got to be back four hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.10,1:00:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked to the center of town.\NThere in the center of town, you look down all four directions in Golden, Colorado.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.10,1:00:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a mountain at the end of each one.\NOn this corner, there's a great big clock like you see in front of a jeweler's clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.13,1:00:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced that before, and yet I'd never been west of the Mississippi.\NBut it was very vivid.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.38,1:00:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I know what deja vu is like.\NI don't know the explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.96,1:00:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you very much.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.40,1:01:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question about the final doorway that you write about in the book, I.\NIs that calibrated?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.40,1:01:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you...\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.40,1:01:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that at level 600 or 850?\NFinal doorway is at 970.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.62,1:01:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When I said final, I mean final.\NBecause for a long time, I was under the impression that it calibrated at 600 because you state
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.80,1:01:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that like Nisargadatta Maharaj went through it, and it seemed unclear that...\NBecause his calibrated level of consciousness was like 720.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.18,1:01:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not the final doorway.\NFinal doorway, you give up life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.20,1:01:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave up their perception of life.\NAnd they surrendered their perception of life to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.40,1:02:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut not life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.35,1:02:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not what the ego believes is life itself, the source of its life.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.80,1:02:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHey, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.75,1:02:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a college student right now, and I'm surrounded by a lot of alcohol and kind of like a party\Nenvironment.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.75,1:02:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Party environment.\NHe's a college student.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.75,1:02:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NParty environment, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.75,1:02:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo my question is, how can you be in that environment and be kind and loving without
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.75,1:02:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,being taken advantage of at the same time?\NKind and loving doesn't mean passive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.38,1:02:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean being a patsy.\NIt means camaraderie and then drawing lines when they're going to go too far.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.35,1:02:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If, let's say, someone keeps peer pressuring you, and finally you just tell them, like,\Nno, is that...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.35,1:03:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody keeps pressuring you?\NYeah, if you're firm, is that...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.35,1:03:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you tell them.\NStill being kind?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.35,1:03:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go along with that.\NI can't go along with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.35,1:03:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI can understand it, but I myself can't go along with it behaviorally, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.48,1:03:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWe all have our own...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.41,1:03:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The way we were brought up, you know, we have our own inbuilt conscience.\NThere's certain things you just can't do and live with yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.41,1:03:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou say, look, I could do it, but then I'd have difficulty with myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.23,1:03:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, what I meant more was, like, when you're saying no, it's not the actual alcohol.\NI just mean if someone was saying something to you and they're kind of pushing you, kind
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.23,1:03:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of pushing your limit, is it okay?\NYou know how you're kind of firm a lot of times when you say no?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.23,1:03:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.23,1:03:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.23,1:03:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.23,1:03:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.23,1:03:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIs it okay to be firm?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.23,1:03:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that still...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.23,1:03:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You just say, you know, I can't go there.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.23,1:03:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NLimits.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.23,1:03:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard being...\NLimits, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.23,1:03:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Limits.\NMy question was about surrender, and you've already answered it, so I just wanted to come
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.23,1:03:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,up and say thank you for the changes in my life.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.23,1:03:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.36,1:03:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.22,1:03:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.07,1:03:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.19,1:04:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.19,1:04:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.19,1:04:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.19,1:04:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.19,1:04:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\Ncaused by the books and tapes you've done.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.67,1:04:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.62,1:04:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the most yellow yellow I've seen all day.\NIs that yellow or is that yellow?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.80,1:04:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She's like a walking dandelion.\NElectric yellow.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.22,1:04:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I had figured out how to ask this a minute ago,\Nbut I can't quite now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.09,1:04:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm the guy that doesn't step on the bugs\Nand picks the dead animals off the road
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.08,1:04:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because I don't like seeing them squished.\NSo then I get this opportunity for a job
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.77,1:05:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that entails protecting the environment,\Nbut part of that is having to eliminate beavers at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.81,1:05:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm thinking this is one of those perception versus essence problems maybe.\NNo, you have to eliminate them.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.54,1:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to be able to move them.\NI just don't want to like end up going back from where I came
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.74,1:05:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and have God say, you know, you were doing so good up until that beaver thing.\NYou draw the line at that which you feel is a violation
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.24,1:05:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of your understanding of the value of life.\NAnd you can tell them, look, I'd be happy to move beavers all day long,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.64,1:05:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but killing them, I can't do it.\NAnd then I get into one of the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.66,1:05:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the thoughts was you're probably just as guilty if you say,\NI'll do all the other stuff, but I'll have somebody else often.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.76,1:05:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can be a conscientious objector.\NDuring the war, we had a couple guys on the ship
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.98,1:06:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that just didn't want to kill anybody,\Nbut they don't mind doing the radio and doing the scribe.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.56,1:06:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could just say, look, I'm a conscientious objector.\NI can't live with a conscience where I feel that I myself have done this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.82,1:06:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, yeah.\NTough, tough one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.12,1:06:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, maybe I should take up woodworking or something instead.\NWell, you just, you have to live with yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.88,1:06:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, you know, it's going to be done.\NIt's going to be done.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.61,1:06:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't have to be the one that does it.\NThat's what I was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.92,1:06:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, World War II, you know,\None of the greatest things for which I thank the Lord
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.30,1:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is I didn't have to kill anybody, you know.\NI was on a minesweeper.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.54,1:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have to kill anybody.\NAnd I would not envy somebody who's in the position where you gotta.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.73,1:07:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, if you gotta,\Nit's more or less taken out of your hands, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.41,1:07:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a difficult one.\NAnd I sympathize with your moral dilemma about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.94,1:07:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me something to think about anyway.\NWell, I guess I thought about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.08,1:07:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be the one that pulls the trigger.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.78,1:07:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, you know, the guillotine's going to come down anyway.\N14.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.46,1:07:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,14,000 were guillotined.\N14,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.89,1:07:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't have to be the one that runs the guillotine.\NNeither are you going to stop the French Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.09,1:07:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought you were going to stop the French Revolution\Nand save the life of all the beavers.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.69,1:07:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't have to be you that runs the guillotine.\NThanks very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.46,1:07:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get a beaver team.\NSmall, small-sized beaver-rama.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.84,1:07:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,14,000 people were chopped off for the guillotine.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.54,1:08:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NI've been grappling all day over which of two questions to ask you,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.86,1:08:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I realize that they're related.\NThree or four times now you've told me directly,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.04,1:08:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,one day I'll be looking at something and divinity will shine forth through it.\NThe other question, which will become obvious,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.99,1:08:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is how do you know when you're not playing in the astral domains?\NI think I'm confused between...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.59,1:08:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Paradigms, almost, because particularly at night there are experiences\Nwhere what seemed harmless, just watching, have turned into not so harmless.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.91,1:08:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I guess I'm kind of confused.\NWhat do you mean, watching?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.03,1:08:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,On television or in your mind?\NNo, seeing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.29,1:08:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NSeeing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.67,1:08:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing what?\NLights, energy patterns.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.27,1:09:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Visions of energy patterns and things like that?\NBut...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.11,1:09:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they benign?\NThey were.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.47,1:09:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I would stick with the benign and refuse all others.\NSo it's okay, it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.53,1:09:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can...\NIt's called the testing of spirits.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.96,1:09:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Either it's benign and of the Christ or not.\NAnd you can challenge the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.80,1:09:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called something, the qualification of the spirits.\NTo acknowledge Jesus Christ as your saviour, yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.10,1:09:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If it says no, you vanish it and get the hints.\NGot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.68,1:09:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's got a formal name in religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.70,1:09:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The qualification or the declaration.\NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.26,1:09:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The provocation of the spirits?\NWho knows it?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.66,1:09:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody Christians here?\NIt's called something.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.36,1:09:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a formal name.\NAll spirits can be challenged.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.92,1:09:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the challenging of spirits.\NDo you acknowledge Jesus Christ as your saviour, yes or no?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.77,1:10:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIf it says yes, then it is of the Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.79,1:10:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it could be, you know, like an angelic form.\NThat which is demonic will not acknowledge Jesus Christ as its saviour.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.46,1:10:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you can vanish it.\NIt's not verbal or anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.24,1:10:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But so...\NYeah, but you can hold that as a...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.30,1:10:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying.\NYou can hold it without verbalizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.70,1:10:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.62,1:10:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You challenge the spirits.\NThat's not playing with the astral circus.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.70,1:10:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already...\NThe circus is already going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.70,1:10:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking me what to do because it's going to enter us.\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.24,1:10:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in the screen doors.\NI'll tell you what to do if they're already in the screen door.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.66,1:10:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I just deny it all?\NI mean, it's just not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.32,1:10:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just challenge spirits or ignore them or order them henceforth.\NDoes this mean I'm distracted for lifetimes?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.88,1:10:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you've warned against the astral circus and I don't know what happened.\NYou know, does this mean this is a distraction off of the goal?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.91,1:11:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I don't want it.\NYou can order them.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.25,1:11:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can order them to leave you.\NIn the name of the Lord Jesus Christ, I order you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.89,1:11:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to leave.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.73,1:11:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can order them.\NYou call upon the Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.63,1:11:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Banish them.\NThat's your right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.77,1:11:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jesus Christ is your savior, is he?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.43,1:11:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you have the right.\NThat's all it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.34,1:11:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you go to church?\NSometimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.12,1:11:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Used to.\NYou have a priest?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.95,1:11:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to let him go.\NYou had to let your priest go?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.69,1:11:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the side or what?\NHe was programming me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.45,1:11:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NA conspiracy theorist.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.46,1:11:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness.\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.94,1:11:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mess.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.78,1:11:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I would just banish the spirits.\NAnd right now, you don't want them even if they're friendly.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.10,1:11:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if they're friendly or not friendly.\NI'm not equipped to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.62,1:11:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My teacher says I should ask you to leave now.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.74,1:12:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NCome back 20, 30 years, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.14,1:12:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But in doing that, I'm not throwing the baby out with the bath.\NI mean, like I can just deny it all and it won't prevent.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.50,1:12:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.46,1:12:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBecause you don't reach enlightenment via that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.18,1:12:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NIs it distracting?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.42,1:12:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a distraction in a way.\NGlad we cleared that up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.25,1:12:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.93,1:12:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll test you out to see if you're friendly\Nuntil they're hanging around and fooling them and playing games with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.01,1:12:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you tell them you're not, they'll leave.\NI didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.83,1:12:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It just was so benign.\NIt was nothing before.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.59,1:12:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDo what I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.73,1:12:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?\NJust do what I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.65,1:12:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NYou have my word.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.15,1:12:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.51,1:12:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThey're seductive by their presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.89,1:12:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Elementals.\NElementals want to play games with their head.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.37,1:12:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.56,1:12:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Seduce her into playing with them.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.40,1:12:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you again.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.12,1:12:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.29,1:13:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's difficult.\NI've been experiencing a lot of changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.58,1:13:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was happening is I used to be very career-oriented,\Nvery success-oriented.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.19,1:13:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm not.\NI don't believe anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.43,1:13:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All my beliefs have fallen away.\NI don't feel I know anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.83,1:13:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm left with no beliefs and not knowing anything.\NAnd right now, I'm trying to go back to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.23,1:13:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know what direction to take.\NDo we have a work that we're supposed to be doing, something we're meant to do, a purposeful
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.65,1:13:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,work?\NOr does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.71,1:13:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's within yourself, your own interests and capabilities.\NAnd you dedicate it to the good of mankind and whatever service you can be, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.71,1:13:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to make a living.\NThat's your obligation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.76,1:13:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're the steward of this body.\NAnd you've got to keep it going.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.80,1:14:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, basically, I'm intelligent, I have skills, I mean, just use those skills.\NYeah, I would use your skills and do what you do best.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.66,1:14:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have mechanical skills, artistic skills, whatever they are.\NHow does this work?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.06,1:14:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, will the, will the, you know, ask God for help, ask God for a miracle, and then it will help to bring me the job?\NOr I go out and look, and I apply to everything?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.39,1:14:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Both will happen.\NBoth will happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.85,1:14:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, with spiritual help.\NWith spiritual help, that which you seek, you'll find, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.19,1:14:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So take action, you say.\NYeah, yeah, they always say take action.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.35,1:14:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, always say take action.\NLike I said, I prayed for a job, and nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.38,1:14:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If it hadn't been for my brother-in-law calling me and offering me a job, I'd still be out there.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.72,1:14:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I get a picture?\NYeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.26,1:15:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.14,1:15:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NGood to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.65,1:15:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed today you calibrated broccoli, and broccoli is doing really well.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.22,1:15:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, I've heard you say back in November that cats and dogs might have an etheric brain, and you didn't know because you hadn't asked.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.76,1:15:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was wondering if you would ask.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.44,1:15:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NFor some reason, we've got to know about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.38,1:15:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Just accept their lovingness as a gift and appreciate them.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.02,1:16:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something yet that I don't know about it.\NI don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.29,1:16:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI was just wondering about their evolution since broccoli is doing so well.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.29,1:16:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBroccoli is a different kind of energy than a cat or a dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.29,1:16:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's more intellectual, mental, although she's very affectionate, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.29,1:16:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.29,1:16:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI was just wondering about the spiritual evolution of cats and dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.29,1:16:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.29,1:16:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand it myself.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.45,1:16:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I sort of have intuitive presumptions about it, but it's something I don't want to know about now.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.90,1:16:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NMaybe 50, 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.90,1:16:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.90,1:16:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NShould I go to Doggyland?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.90,1:16:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They're obviously a gift to us.\NMany people would have committed suicide if it wasn't for their pet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.90,1:16:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?\NHi, Dr. Huggins.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.04,1:16:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NI wanted to ask you to describe Joppa, playing Joppa.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.36,1:16:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Joppa?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.36,1:16:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to know about it?\NWell, I want to know if I'm doing it right and if ...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.93,1:16:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a Joppa teacher.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.93,1:16:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a Joppa teacher.\NI'm not a Joppa teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.93,1:16:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a Joppa teacher.\NI'm not a Joppa teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.64,1:17:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a Joppa teacher.\NI'm not a Joppa teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.64,1:17:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you doing it?\NI do it ... I don't do it consistently, and that's maybe partly why I wanted to ask you
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.64,1:17:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.\NMaybe I wanted to ... I think I wanted to know if I really should continue to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.64,1:17:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What attracted you to it?\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.64,1:17:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it helps me kind of not be frightened sometimes.\NOh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.76,1:17:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps me to stay focused, that sort of thing.\NWell, it calibrates well, so it's the same as I think it's praying, saying the Lord's
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.76,1:17:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.76,1:17:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.76,1:17:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.76,1:17:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.76,1:17:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.40,1:17:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.40,1:17:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.40,1:17:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.40,1:17:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.40,1:17:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.40,1:17:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.40,1:17:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.40,1:17:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAbout the same effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.40,1:17:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay, so it's like a ..
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.40,1:17:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It pulls up that spiritual energy, and then that spiritual energy, where would\Nit look frightening or a problem, doesn't look frightening like a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.40,1:17:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NYeah, actually, that's what it does for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.40,1:17:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because it pulls up that energy.\NAnd is it in the sound that that happens?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.40,1:17:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I haven't researched it to that detail.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.42,1:17:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that helps, though.\NThat is why ..
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.38,1:17:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt pulls up that field because of the intention, and that field, then recontextualizes
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.14,1:18:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and reframes it, so it looks different.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.40,1:18:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Up, up, up, up, up, up, buddy. Remember in kindergarten? Up, up, up, up, buddy, buddy.\NHello, Dr. Hawkins. Before I started reading your books, which I consider my most practical
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.04,1:18:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual help now, I studied the works of L.S.A. Bailey and Helena Polatsky since my\Nyouth, and I enjoyed particularly their exposition on cosmology, cosmogenesis, and so on, which
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.50,1:19:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't get into. I was just wondering, I didn't see them on your slide about spiritual\Nteachers. How would you rate them? I didn't have the White Brotherhood on there, no, or
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.54,1:19:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice Bailey, no. I didn't have the White Brotherhood. Or the Theosophical Teachings\Nas such. Oh, Theosophical, yes, yes. Polatsky in particular has, you know, the Secret Doctrine.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.08,1:19:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I didn't do Polatsky, no. I consider she's way up there. And Alice Bailey, of course,\Nis part of her.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.51,1:19:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other works were Cosmic Fire, which gets into cosmology. It's just marvelous.\NI'm interested in becoming enlightened, not cosmology.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.82,1:19:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a particular field which interests me, but what you have to offer is the most\Npractical, the most helpful. So if in the future time, if in the future time you decide
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.79,1:19:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to calibrate those.\NWell, I didn't do them all. You know, we did Alice Bailey's book Glamour, and I did Alice
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.79,1:19:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Bailey's.\NYes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.63,1:20:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it explains a lot that without that explanation would be more harder to understand.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.63,1:20:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBless you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.63,1:20:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I respect the White Brotherhood.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.63,1:20:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for being here. A little closer.\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.63,1:20:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Well, I've been studying your work for several years, and this haunting question\Nhas come back that I suspect is problematic.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.18,1:20:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhat I suspect is probably my ego's, the fear of the death of the ego. And it's around,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.34,1:20:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wrote it so that I wouldn't, because it was very hard for me to put these thoughts\Ntogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.44,1:20:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's about my recall of some of the writings that you have talked about over 600, when
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.18,1:21:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we have no more form after we leave this body. That there's, after 600, even up to the 50,000,\Nwhat is it, the Archangels at 50,000?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.18,1:21:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThere's no form.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.18,1:21:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAnd so that means there's no experiencer. That means, of course, there's no-
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.18,1:21:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no what?\NNo experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.22,1:21:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.22,1:21:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, the question is, how does one know that we exist without an experiencer?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.22,1:21:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. There is the knowingness of existence without experiencing. Because you're already\Nputting non-ego in terms of the ego, and then asking me how come.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.13,1:21:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat's the manipulation of the thought form, see? The knowingness of existence is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.27,1:22:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,not a me knowing of that fact. That means the ego would still persist. There would be\Nme, the ego, making a statement about its state called existence. You see, the dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.77,1:22:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no this being a that, see? The thing is what it is, and it's completely fulfilled\Nin what it is without making a statement. It doesn't say I am. It does not say I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.15,1:22:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is. So, its existence is at one with its form. So, having form doesn't preclude\Nexcept that it doesn't know that. It has no consciousness. So, there's the conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.80,1:23:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness of existence without form. In fact, in that conscious awareness is the awareness,\Nthat it's because of I, consciousness, that any awareness of form can take place. Without
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.56,1:23:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,me, there would be no form. Without the knower of the form, there is no form. You understand?\NSo, does that explain what happens when we go into the void then, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.96,1:23:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo? Because we still try to manufacture some kind of form when we go in? No?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.18,1:23:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you talking about the void?\NWell, no, but I guess that's the fear the ego has somewhere along the line that if there's
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.50,1:23:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,no form.\NThe ego fears nothingness. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.50,1:23:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. And so, that's what all of this revolves around.\NSo, it hangs on to form because it thinks without form it will cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.50,1:23:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.50,1:23:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd it's a fact. It will.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.98,1:23:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYes, it feels fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.88,1:24:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, indeed it is.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.43,1:24:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, indeed it is. Then the ego is.\NSo, then you experience out the fear. And then, because all fear is illusion, the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.78,1:24:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,takes the place of the illusion.\NOkay. Experience it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.32,1:24:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.98,1:24:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego feels that without form it will cease to exist.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.98,1:24:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it identifies the form.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.98,1:24:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.08,1:24:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's got more to say besides form.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.08,1:24:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah. It's got more to say.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.08,1:24:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell the ego, you won't run out of juice when you run out of form. You'll think of\Nsome other sneaky way to be around it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.08,1:24:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll claim to be the author of formlessness, so you'll see. It's got more games.\NIt's got more games in its pocket to pull out.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.08,1:24:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.08,1:24:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up that.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.08,1:24:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.77,1:24:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.77,1:24:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.77,1:24:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.77,1:24:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.22,1:24:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.28,1:25:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.34,1:25:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NHey.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.81,1:25:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to start a conversation.\NThat's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.80,1:25:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.80,1:25:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?\NGreetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.80,1:25:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NNamaste.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.80,1:25:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Your book has brought tremendous joy to my heart.\NI'm glad of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.80,1:25:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It opened my eyes to other teachings that I did not have the validity from them to know\Nthat there was truth in that material.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.60,1:25:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.56,1:25:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things I'm starting to experience is fear in meditation, that there's something\Nafter me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.26,1:25:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NI experienced it a week ago when I was in the woods of Virginia, alone at night, and in the silence, the fear came up.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.51,1:25:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, uh-huh. That's the child coming up in you. That was the child.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.76,1:26:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the child? That's the child coming up. Yeah, it was the child coming up in you.\NWhat avenue should I pursue to find what is bringing that up? I'll call you soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.90,1:26:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You speak to the child in reassuring terms, and know that all fear is illusion.\NCorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.74,1:26:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got to persist fear of what?\NFear of itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.67,1:26:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear of fear?\NFear of fear, or fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.41,1:26:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. Yeah, well, just keep surrendering that, and it'll negate itself. It'll resolve itself.\NBecause all fear is based on illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.79,1:26:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBecause the risk is going to happen to you as you die.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.70,1:26:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You said, yeah, well, wouldn't that make you afraid?\NNo. You don't have to be afraid of dying, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.40,1:26:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying? You can chase fear right down to its nub, and undo it.\NOkay. I will practice that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.51,1:27:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one other I may ask. There's a lot of information that you've brought forth to this world.\NIt gives us credence. How would you like to see, excuse me, back up.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.25,1:27:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in and out of AA. I'm familiar with Bill Williams.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.91,1:27:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I went back with a friend that had been...\Nusing drugs, and been back into the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.51,1:27:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I see it as being a springboard that could be used to increase the spiritual awareness on this planet.\NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.65,1:27:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it does calculate at 540.\NThat's for sure. That's pretty high.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.37,1:27:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you given it, or considered, or looked in that direction on how you would like to see your material increased on this planet?\NAnd one that I see is in chaos at some points, in ignorance, and have problems coming ahead of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.07,1:27:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOr have problems that...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.35,1:27:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Or have problems that might come ahead.\NWhere, the planet?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.49,1:28:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In the near future, the planet itself.\NYeah. Well, I think grassroots spirituality is based on practical, experiential reality such as the 12-step groups...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.50,1:28:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.\N...have a subtle profound effect that seeps out into society.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.80,1:28:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I think AA actually influences society. One reason we calibrate what we do is because of the influence of AA subtly on all kinds of ways which people don't know.\NYou know...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.64,1:28:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\N...people don't know the announcer they're listening to.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.16,1:28:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.\NIt's been sober 22 years, and they don't know who's in AA.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.48,1:28:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But that integrity spreads out as an example to the world,\Nand I think it uplifts mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.56,1:28:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think the consciousness of America would be the same without AA.\NI see that from where I'm coming from,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.82,1:28:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I see because of your association with Bill W. at one time\Nthat the group itself, if it was made aware,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.50,1:28:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,made is the wrong word, brought aware of the material that you've brought forward,\Nthat it could grow a lot quicker than what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.86,1:28:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they all blend together, and each one supports the other.\NOf course, the miracles of AA and this work,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.02,1:29:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, they're grassroots.\NIt's not a formal structure or building or anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.86,1:29:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and those kind of things tend to become more pervasive.\NThat which has structure and form tends to create a resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.73,1:29:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has no structure and no form\Nand no...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.61,1:29:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No program and no agenda that's trying to sell anybody\Ndoesn't create resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.47,1:29:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.\NIf a guy wants to be honest on the job
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.21,1:29:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and be an example to others by his honesty and his friendliness,\Nthere's no defense against that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.39,1:29:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't even know he's in AA, you know.\NYes, I have run into some resistance through some statements I've made,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.79,1:29:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or subtle statements, but there is resistance to it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.42,1:29:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's better not to label it.\NDon't call it AA or anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.38,1:29:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.88,1:30:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.16,1:30:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For about maybe six months to a year now,\NI've been kind of on a rollercoaster of going in and out of like
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.36,1:30:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what I consider like a high spiritual state\Nand then like a dropping into kind of a low depressive state,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.88,1:30:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe kind of like a dark night of the soul.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.18,1:30:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm curious if you have like any advice for...\NYeah, you're just living through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.74,1:30:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can expect that.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.04,1:30:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because you rise above your karma.\NNow, because of the good karma, you're entitled to bring up the next stack.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.58,1:30:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens is the next stack comes up.\NYou think you're getting worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.88,1:30:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo, you've got the power and the strength now to handle that stack.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.78,1:30:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go through one stack after another.\NThey eventually clear up.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.76,1:30:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.60,1:31:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It can seem like a lot at times.\NHey, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.72,1:31:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time I was here, I was telling you about my...\NEgo issues, and you told me to not do, and I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.72,1:31:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I not did very well.\NAnd I quit my job, and life is in a very big changing moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.54,1:31:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I feel that there's a concern that maybe this surrender is really maybe a recklessness,\Na shunning of spiritual responsibility maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.90,1:31:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it's like my spiritual policeman saying,\NHey, be on the ball.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.54,1:31:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, surrender means surrendering, trying to control the world.\NAnd that's the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.08,1:31:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But the effort, of course, is dependent on your spiritual level and your commitment.\NBecause the way I've been going about it is like surrendering to the current of the river of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.72,1:31:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd just flowing in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.96,1:31:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWhatever happens, happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.80,1:31:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo I don't know if maybe that's a little too cavalier,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.20,1:32:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or is that the ego is just begging for that last bit of control?\NLike, you can't do it without me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.50,1:32:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, surrender is different than passivity.\NJust make...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.19,1:32:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You think about that, or look at that.\NBecause sometimes surrender means surrendering to a responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.20,1:32:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, surrendering your resistance to the fact that you've got a responsibility.\NSo look at those shades in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.94,1:32:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I think your problem is in there somewhere.\NThat works for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.17,1:32:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI love you guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.96,1:32:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality is more than truth.\NAnd I don't believe in politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.08,1:32:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't going to vote.\NAnd you go like another would say, well, my responsibility as a spiritually integrous person is to vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.04,1:32:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know.\NI think it depends on which facet of the diamond you're looking at.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.60,1:32:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.62,1:33:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a good friend that's becoming, like, increasingly negative.\NAnd I don't want to, like, play with fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.07,1:33:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it's better to avoid him or to try to understand him.\NIf you understand what's going on with him, it can help.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.30,1:33:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only do that if you understand.\NIf you don't understand and he's going into a negative direction,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.76,1:33:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you're probably going to have to part.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.19,1:33:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.76,1:33:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOh, I brought you a thank you letter, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.19,1:33:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.60,1:33:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking about this question.\NAnd in my own spiritual quest, I mean, I've kind of been trying to figure out what's the purpose of any negativity at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.52,1:34:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In the whole spectrum of reality, it seems like, okay, well, and I've thought of this, you know,\Nwhy not just existence and consciousness being so pure and perfect in its own essence?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.86,1:34:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, why?\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.40,1:34:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.24,1:34:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why have this contradicting force that we have to go through?\NAnd, like, the one thing that I have came to, like, the conclusion is maybe it's so you can actually recognize
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.90,1:34:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,how sweet enlightenment really is once you get there.\NBut, I mean, it's so painful to have to go through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.54,1:34:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, I'm just...\NPainful to go through what?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.80,1:34:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To go through all of the downfalls and everything you have to, all of these, this craziness and madness\Nbefore you can actually get that clarity, which I'm starting to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.14,1:34:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NAnd so, I mean, like, what is the ultimate?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.99,1:34:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to figure out what...\NWhat would you say is the ultimate purpose of negativity in any way?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.27,1:34:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if God is the consciousness and love within everything...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.41,1:34:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why...\NWhat's negativity doing there?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.09,1:34:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, we looked at the chart showing the evolution of consciousness, and we saw that mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.08,1:35:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is on a rising curve, and you're part of mankind.\NSo, along with mankind, you are, like, transcending the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.48,1:35:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The temptation to hate, you're turning it down now.\NThe temptation for greed, you're turning it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.80,1:35:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The temptation for envy.\NSo, they have to come up for you to transcend them and turn them down.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.96,1:35:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that they're bad.\NIt's just that you've made a decision to be otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.14,1:35:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.10,1:35:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSo, it's normal.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.16,1:35:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Normal what you're going through.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.83,1:35:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThank you, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.92,1:35:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, 12-step groups, they call...\NThey have what they call the fourth step.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.20,1:35:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You take a spiritual inventory.\NYou take a long, yellow...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.13,1:35:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Legal-sized tablet.\NYou start writing down all your character defects.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.83,1:35:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Hawkins.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.26,1:36:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book, Transcending Level of Consciousness, the section about temptations from different\Nlevel of consciousness, under this level, ecstasy, you list poor judgment as a temptation.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.65,1:36:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you please elaborate on this?\NWhat do you mean by poor judgment?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.51,1:36:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a temptation.\NIt's not a temptation, but it's one quality that the downside of ecstasy is to lead to
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.11,1:36:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,excessive behaviors.\NExcessive behaviors.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.85,1:36:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, each side has its upside and its downside.\NEcstasy could lead you to taking off all your clothes and deciding you can fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.27,1:36:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And people on LSD did that.\NThey go in a state of ecstasy, take off their clothes, and expect to fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.49,1:36:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the downside is brash foolishness.\NTherefore, you constantly surrender your ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.37,1:36:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The ecstasy is coming from the awareness of the presence of God as the source of your\Nexistence, and the totality of all that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.59,1:37:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's ecstatic when that suddenly dawns on you, because it breaks through, like, overwhelming.\NAnd you're just stunned by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.42,1:37:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the possibility would be to go into an ecstatic state and have it mistaken as catatonia\Nor something.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.01,1:37:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me put you away.\NSo, what can we do to kind of guard against that kind of irrationality?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.63,1:37:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.\NDon't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.25,1:37:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If they put you away, you haven't called me, I'll find you.\NThat's a good advice.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.21,1:37:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAppreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.49,1:37:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThis guy is in a state of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.27,1:37:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do with him, Doc?\NWe're done.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.21,1:37:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to quit now.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.25,1:37:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got just a couple more.\NWe've got four minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.85,1:37:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we do.\NIt's four minutes to five.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.19,1:37:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.\NIt's five o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.39,1:37:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got four minutes to five.\NMine is atomic time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.49,1:37:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, hurry.\NYou've got to hurry, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.69,1:37:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk fast.\NSpeak fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.13,1:38:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI've been studying the keys of Enoch.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.92,1:38:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You did not calibrate it very high.\NI was drawn to it because of the level of scientific complexity and the possibilities
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.19,1:38:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of connecting with someone who has been or re-spatialized to higher levels of being.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.59,1:38:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you comment on this any more about that?\NWe calibrated the keys of Enoch and all I can tell you is what it calibrated at.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.17,1:38:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget now.\NIt's in the book, Truth Versus Falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.19,1:38:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd have you experienced the other, you were talking about the low levels that you're not
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.41,1:38:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating, but have you experienced yourself higher levels with the ascended masters and\Nthe grids of being?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.27,1:38:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,See, those are celestial realms.\NI don't go into the realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.10,1:38:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They all have their own hierarchy.\NDo you think it's possible for us as humans to go there?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.91,1:38:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's an infinite number of celestial realms and other dimensions.\NIn this lifetime, I don't have the time to go into them because what can any one of them
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.73,1:39:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,offer you?\NEnlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.03,1:39:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than enlightenment, none of them have anything to offer you.\NSo leave the celestial realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.11,1:39:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,From this dimension, you can reach salvation through Jesus Christ.\NYou can reach the enlightenment through the pathway of the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.01,1:39:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NYou can reach Krishna consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.90,1:39:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does another dimension?\NThat to offer you other than novelty and cutesy ideas and weird names for the divinity of
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.34,1:39:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that dimension, et cetera.\NI'll ponder that.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.31,1:39:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing beyond salvation, redemption, and enlightenment, is there?\NSo what is the keys to any kind of a weird other dimension going to offer you other than
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.82,1:39:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,novelty?\NLet's say I call the head of my dimension Ugg.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.56,1:39:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NWe all worship Ugg.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.29,1:39:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So?\NFirst of all, you don't live in that dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.28,1:40:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You live in this dimension.\NSo Ugg isn't going to do you any good anyway because you're not an Ugg-ian.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.90,1:40:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I live in Ugg.\NYou're a human-ian.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.40,1:40:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got Jesus Christ, you've got the Buddha, you've got Krishna, what more do you need?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.56,1:40:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we do have...\NYou're looking for big animals and you've got an elephant in your living room.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.45,1:40:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.\NWhat are you pushing me for?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.48,1:40:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not under a compulsion to walk out the door at this stroke.\NWe've only got a couple of people left.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.48,1:40:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.\NMove.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.13,1:40:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Move.\NMove.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.13,1:40:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Move.\NMove.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.13,1:40:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Move.\NMove.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.13,1:40:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Move.\NCome on, move along.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.92,1:40:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NWell, let me thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.92,1:40:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBecause you've helped contextualize what happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.24,1:41:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a 28-day program when I realized that I was in the same boat as everybody else,\Nand that really I couldn't really...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.90,1:41:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know any of the truth from falsehood.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.20,1:41:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And neither did anybody else.\NAnd I went back to my room.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.47,1:41:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went on my knees, and I just asked to just know, like to get better.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.42,1:41:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I lost track of things.\NAnd how could I put that?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.69,1:41:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt this energy.\NThat's why I could connect with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.20,1:41:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the therapist knew that there was something fairly drastic happened to me.\NAnd I knew that I couldn't function in the world like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.73,1:41:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I still had young kids at home.\NAnd he asked me to pull back, because I was going to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.74,1:42:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't think I could function.\NSo I did pull back.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.64,1:42:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was there to listen to what I was told.\NI made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.88,1:42:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I listened.\NAnd I pulled back, went back to my mind, thinking and everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.47,1:42:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even have to think then.\NAnd I didn't know what happened, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.27,1:42:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know.\NIn reading your books now, I do know what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.78,1:42:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that I just...\NI'm back at that point now.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.62,1:42:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to what point?\NThat I can just feel the energy up my back.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.63,1:42:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All over, it's burning.\NHave you recovered from the purpose for which you went there?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.37,1:42:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I haven't had a drink, nothing ever since.\NSo you're doing very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.09,1:42:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMorning in.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.68,1:42:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the question that I have is this here.\NI'm at the point where I feel like what I have to do next...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.92,1:43:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just feel the energy and just do what I do best.\NI'm a businessman.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.72,1:43:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you do.\NAnd just feel the energy and don't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.60,1:43:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Just feel it.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.96,1:43:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.72,1:43:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NGood spot on the turn around, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.82,1:43:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NBefore I started on my spiritual path, I had a relatively good sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.57,1:43:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm starting to take things so seriously.\NSuggestions for recouping my sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.13,1:43:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So logically, I've done.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.28,1:43:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a period where you go through it serious, you know.\NThen there's a period where it's humorous again.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.50,1:43:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And later on, you get serious about your humor.\NThen you think getting serious about your humor itself is humorous.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.48,1:44:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Which in itself is a serious matter, is it not?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.26,1:44:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think humor is of divine origin.\NWe're all done, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.96,1:44:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.44,1:44:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more, isn't there?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.38,1:44:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Huggins.\NI'd first like to thank you for your teachings and you've helped me a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.76,1:44:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what I would do without you, to be honest.\NI just had a question about my own intentions, my own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.74,1:44:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd I'm just worried my own intentions, I'm worried about my own intentions and my own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.92,1:44:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own what?\NIntentions.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.60,1:44:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Intentions?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.46,1:44:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What they are.\NYour motivations.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.80,1:44:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Use different languages.\NIntention doesn't mean much to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.14,1:44:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWhat do you want to, what's your goal?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.30,1:44:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Define your intention by your goal.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.28,1:44:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To be more loving, more patient.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.70,1:45:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,More generous towards others.\NTo ask for a miracle instead of trying to control things.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.98,1:45:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.62,1:45:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You just apply that everywhere you've learned.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.39,1:45:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd then the consequences will come about as a result of what you've become.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.37,1:45:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The field begins to expand.\NAnd then the field lifts you like a balloon.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.24,1:45:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt isn't like you cause yourself to rise.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.04,1:45:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NBut by the raising of your spiritual intention, you like change your buoyancy.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.60,1:45:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you sort of begin to float up in the field where the same field other people have drowned, you float.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.54,1:45:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see others drown in the same field in which you float.\NThat's happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.90,1:45:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's happened.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.22,1:45:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's a curiosity.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.81,1:45:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NWhy is it some go down and others go up in exactly the same field?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.41,1:45:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.79,1:45:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because your intention, your buoyancy is different.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.40,1:45:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Dr. Hawkins.\NLove you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.62,1:46:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.34,1:46:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NI give thanks to Almighty God for the joy of your presence and your love, which is God's gift to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.78,1:46:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You are all God's gift to me.\NThank you, God, for all these wonderful people.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.66,1:46:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\NGod bless you.
